.Sh BUGS
Media types are hardcoded
.Pq see the Li getContentType() No function
and determined solely by file extension.
A more exhaustive and intelligent system should be used for identifying \
the content-type of served files.
.Pp
A dedicated facility for transferring files from the client to the host needs \
to be added; the current method of setting the
.Fl -print-post
switch and redirecting
.Nm Ap s
output to a file is plainly idiotic and unintuitive,
not to mention time-consuming: the
.Li multipart/form-data
payload that's written to the filesystem requires one to untangle its contents \
using a binary editor,
as the combination of
.Tn ASCII
and binary data makes splitting on boundary strings in JavaScript unfeasible.
A rewrite is already in the works on a detached branch at GitHub.
.Pp
The code for mapping requests to files and/or redirects is a confusing mess.
It's also inflexible;
a configurable mechanism for URL routing should be provided.
.Pp
JavaScript files used as entry-points should have a predefined
.Vt argv
global populated by the URL's query variables.
